description: From Latin preternātūrālis/praeternātūrālis, from praeter nātūram, from praeter (“beyond”) + nātūra (“nature”); compare supernatural.

adjectives.description: preternatural (comparative more preternatural, superlative most preternatural)

entries.meaning: Beyond or not conforming to what is natural or according to the regular course of things; strange.
examples: Synonyms: inexplicable, exceptional, extraordinary, abnormal, uncanny

entries.meaning: (dated) Having an existence outside of the natural world.
